; place-sense.fk — turn a reverse-geocoded coordinate into WORLD SENSE: name where you are, know how
; specific that knowing is, recognize a place you've been before (presence continuity), and relate
; places by containment. The carrier reverse-geocodes a coordinate to a hierarchy (OpenStreetMap's
; Nominatim, no API key needed) — country / state / county / city / suburb / road / house; this recipe
; is the BODY that makes meaning of that hierarchy. Carrier fetches; Form understands.
;
; A place is a list of (rank name) levels ordered COARSE -> FINE: rank is the integer admin depth
; (0 country, 1 state/region, 2 county, 3 city, 4 suburb, 5 neighbourhood, 6 road, 7 house), name the
; string at that level. Same named hierarchy => same place on every body — the content-addressed
; identity the substrate promises, so "I am at the same place as before" comes for free, by shape, not
; by a hopeful coordinate match. (Coordinates are noisy and never repeat exactly; named places do.)
;
; THE SENSES this gives (Urs: location, presence, world):
;   - LOCATION: pl-name is the most specific name we can give where we are; pl-scale how specific.
;   - PRESENCE: pl-same? recognizes two reads as the same place; pl-known? recognizes a place among the
;     ones we remember — "I have been here before", the continuity a presence needs.
;   - WORLD: pl-within? relates places by scale (this road is within that city) — the nesting that makes
;     a world model rather than a scatter of points.
;
; Integers + strings only; no coordinates, no float, no distance — recognition is by NAMED SHAPE, which
; is the honest and stable thing a noisy fix can be resolved to. Great-circle distance / nearest-feature
; (Overpass, also no key) is a later organ; this is the naming-and-recognition core.
;
; Kin: journey.fk (the track whose endpoints these name), spatial-fusion.fk (banded the fix that was
; geocoded), world-model-growth.fk (ingests these place cells into the growing world model), the
; substrate's content-addressing (same shape -> same NodeID). Carrier-last: the phone/host fetches the
; geocode; place-sense is Form, four-way-identical.
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk
;
; Proven by: form-stdlib/tests/place-sense-band.fk (four-way at validate.sh)

(do
    ; a level is (rank name): (nth lv 0) the integer admin depth, (nth lv 1) the name string.

    ; --- NAME: the most specific (deepest / last) level's name — what to call where we are. ---
    (defn pl-name (place)
        (if (eq (len place) 1) (nth (head place) 1) (pl-name (tail place))))

    ; --- SCALE: the deepest level's rank — how specific the knowing is (0 country .. 7 house). ---
    (defn pl-scale (place)
        (if (eq (len place) 1) (nth (head place) 0) (pl-scale (tail place))))

    ; --- DEPTH: how many levels are named. ---
    (defn pl-depth (place) (len place))

    ; --- SAME?: two reads are the same place when they name to the same depth and the same deepest
    ;     name — recognition by shape, the presence-continuity "still here / here again". ---
    (defn pl-same? (a b)
        (if (eq (pl-depth a) (pl-depth b))
            (if (str_eq (pl-name a) (pl-name b)) 1 0)
            0))

    ; --- WITHIN?: is `inner` inside `outer` — i.e. outer's whole level-chain is a prefix of inner's
    ;     (this road within that city). Walk both coarse->fine; every outer level must match. ---
    (defn pl-within? (inner outer)
        (if (eq (len outer) 0) 1
            (if (eq (len inner) 0) 0
                (if (eq (nth (head inner) 0) (nth (head outer) 0))
                    (if (str_eq (nth (head inner) 1) (nth (head outer) 1))
                        (pl-within? (tail inner) (tail outer))
                        0)
                    0))))

    ; --- KNOWN?: is this place among the ones we remember — "I have been here before". ---
    (defn pl-known? (place known)
        (if (eq (len known) 0) 0
            (if (eq (pl-same? place (head known)) 1) 1 (pl-known? place (tail known)))))

    0)
